Class Song

  • java.lang.Object
    • lusc.net.github.Song

  • public class Song
extends java.lang.Object
    Song is the object that recording units are held in. It contains both acoustic recording data and measured sub-units like elements and syllables. It contains methods to make spectrograms. It is one of the most central classes in Luscinia, and one of the largest.
    Author:
    Rob

      • interpretSyllables

        public void interpretSyllables()
        This method takes a set of syllables, and parses them into phrases. It searches for syllables that encompass other syllables, and makes them markers of phrases. It produces a linked list of phrases. Each item if this is an int[][]. The first index represents the number of repeats of a syllable within a phrase, and the second indicates which elements from eleList belong to that syllable. This method imposes quite strict limits on patterns of hierarchical organization in song. It is used extensively by analysis methods, but it would be better to revise it to be more flexible.

      • getPhase

        public double[] getPhase()
        gets a phase matrix, indicating the support of a given input frequency for a hypothesized pitch. i.e. integer multiples of fundamental frequencies are given a large weight.
        Returns:
        a double[] representing phase
